When working with Vue.js frontend code, use the following rules:

1. Always use Vue Single-File Components (SFCs) for all Vue components.
2. All <style> tags should be scoped to the component.
3. All CSS styles should use SCSS syntax, and the <style> tag should have the lang="scss" attribute.
4. The CSS framework to use is Bootstrap 5.
5. CSS should be structured in a mobile-first approach.

When working with the Python backend, use the following rules:

1. All newly generated Python functions should include simple docstrings under the function declaration.